## Quest Design

### Quest Schema

```typescript
interface Quest {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  type: "ESCORT" | "HUNT" | "GATHER" | "INVESTIGATE" | "MANHUNT" | "SECT" | "HIDDEN";

  narrative: {
    hook: string;           // How the quest is presented
    objective: string;       // Clear statement of what to do
    completion: string;     // Success message
    failure: string;         // Failure message
  };

  requirements: QuestRequirement;

  duration: {
    type: "INSTANT" | "TIMED" | "ONGOING";
    hours?: number;
  };

  risk: "NONE" | "LOW" | "MEDIUM" | "HIGH";

  rewards: QuestReward[];

  impact: QuestImpact;       // How this affects the world
}

interface QuestImpact {
  factionRelations?: Record<string, number>;
  regionState?: Record<string, unknown>;
  unlocksQuest?: string;
  closesQuest?: string;
}
```

### Quest Design Rules

1. **Every quest has a clear goal** — "Collect 5 Dược Thảo" not "Help the herbalist"
2. **Every quest has meaningful choice** — Even escort quests can have: fight, negotiate, or flee
3. **Every quest has consequence** — Success, partial success, or failure each have outcomes
4. **Rewards match risk** — No "slay the dragon" quests with herb rewards
5. **Quests can chain** — Completing one unlocks the next
6. **Quests can conflict** — Some quests are mutually exclusive

